Reasoning: 
1. cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) - The paper deals with the encoding of classical sequent calculus into the Pi-calculus, which is a topic related to logic in computer science. 
2. cs.PL (Programming Languages) - The Pi-calculus is a process calculus used for modeling concurrent systems, which is a topic related to programming languages. 
3. cs.LOgic (Logic in Computer Science) - The paper defines a notion of type assignment using the type constructor "arrow", which is a topic related to logic in computer science. 
4. cs.SE (Software Engineering) - The paper deals with the encoding of circuits into the Pi-calculus, which is a topic related to software engineering. 
5. cs.TCS (Theoretical Computer Science) - The paper deals with the encoding of a calculus into another calculus, which is a topic related to theoretical computer science.
